<DOCNO> XIE19980923.0001 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-23 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tajik Opposition Leader Killed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, September 22 (Xinhua) -- The leader of the Unified
Tajik Opposition was killed in the republic's capital of Dushanbe
on Tuesday morning, said an Itar-Tass news agency report.
</P>
<P>
Otakhon Latifi, chairman of a subcommission for legal issues
under the Commission for National Reconciliation, was shot to
death when he was leaving his house in the center of the city.
</P>
<P>
There were no details about the murder. And the source
interviewed by Itar-Tass refused to give any comments.
</P>
<P>
Latifi came to Dushanbe together with other opposition members
of the commission in September 1997.
</P>
<P>
He was a correspondent of the Pravda newspaper for Tajikistan
in the 1970s and 1980s. In the early 1990s, he was deputy prime
minister in the national reconciliation government.
</P>
<P>
While condemning the killing, the United Nations mission in
Tajikistan said Latifi made a significant contribution to the
peace process of the former Soviet republic.
</P>
<P>
The U.N. mission called on the Tajik government and the
opposition to adhere to their commitments on the peace process.
</P>
<P>
The Russian foreign ministry also condemned the murder, saying
the event shows there are forces in Tajikistan that are not
interested in the stabilization of the country's situation.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980923.0002 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-23 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Turkmenistan Sticks to One-China Policy: President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALMA ATA, September 22 (Xinhua) -- Turkman President Saparmurad
Niyazov Monday reiterated that Taiwan is an inalienable part of
the People's Republic of China and that his country will never
acknowledge "two Chinas" or "one China, one Taiwan."
</P>
<P>
The president also said his country will never establish any
political relations with Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
Niyazov made the statement in a meeting with newly appointed
Chinese Ambassador to Turkmenistan, Gong Liefu, who was presenting
credentials to him.
</P>
<P>
Niyazov stressed that Turkmenistan is opposed to Pan-Turkism,
to the use of territories of one country to conduct activities to
separate another country, and to the interference of internal
affairs of other nations under the pretext of religious beliefs.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
