<HEADLINE> U.N. Agencies Call for Aid to China's Flood-Hit Areas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, September 22 (Xinhua) -- The World Health Organization
(WHO) and the World Food Organization (WFO) Tuesday called for
raising a total aid of 107 million U.S. dollars to help victims of
the recent floods hitting parts of China.
</P>
<P>
WHO spokesman Philippe Stroot said here that his organization
is appealing for raising 13 million U.S. dollars to buy
antibiotic, physiological saline, disinfectant for water and
pesticide for the Chinese victims.
</P>
<P>
Christiane Berthiaume, spokeswoman of WFO, said her
organization would call for raising an aid of 87 million
U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
She said that in the next four months, it is necessary to
provide the victims with 247,000 tons of food and temporary
houseing. 
</P>
</TEXT>
