his department has worked out relief plans to offer goods to
people in addition to the implementation of small-scale
production programs.
</P>
<P>
Zamissa said that from this September to next April,
Mozambique will need 41,600 tons of maize and 3,700 tons of beans
to overcome the food shortage facing the country.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, various seeds including 818 tons of rice, 978 tons
of bean, 2,000 tons of maize, 789 tons of peanut, 519 tons of
sorghum and 163 tons of millet will also be needed, he added.
