<HEADLINE> Sudan Intensifies Fight Against Malaria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KHARTOUM, September 22 (Xinhua) -- Sudanese President Omar
al-Bashir Tuesday issued a decree on promoting the national
campaign against malaria, a big killer disease in Sudan for long.
</P>
<P>
The decree provides for setting up a political committee for
providing financial and executive support for the campaign.
</P>
<P>
Under the decree, a coordination committee will be formed with
the aim of supervising the implementation of the anti-malaria
national program.
</P>
<P>
It urged the mass media, and the federal and provincial
departments to contribute to the sanitary educational program
against malaria. The decree also called for popular support for
the campaign.
</P>
<P>
Earlier this month, Sudan started a national campaign for
malaria-combat with a view to removing the epidemic completely by
the start of the next century.
</P>
<P>
The campaign covers the activities of draining off the recent
flood waters, combating the mosquito organisms, spraying
long-effect pesticides in the farm areas.  
</P>
