<DOCNO> XIE19980923.0052 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-23 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Angola to Implement Licensing System in Trade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, September 22 (Xinhua) -- Angola has decided to
implement a licensing system in merchandise trading, the Angolan
News Agency Tuesday quoted sources from the ministry of planning
as saying.
</P>
<P>
The sources said that the licensing system in import
and export is aimed at strengthening the state "control of the
currency and exchange rate."
</P>
<P>
Under the new rule, any exchange of merchandise goods between
local residents and foreigners will be regarded as import or
export trading.
</P>
<P>
Such activities will be put under the regulation of the
licensing system. The icense for import or export will be
issued by the Trade Ministry and the ministry will also be
monitoring the legality of the ensuing trade.
</P>
<P>
No license will be needed for the import or export involving
only provisional trading or trading with small quantity,
according to the new rule.
</P>
<P>
Other activities enjoy the exemption of license include the
provision of goods and logistics services for foreign maritime or
air shipping companies.
</P>
<P>
The licenses are effective within 180 days after issuance and
their effectiveness could be extended to the longest of 360 days,
the new rule reads.
</P>
<P>
The National Bank of Angola will notify the Trade Ministry of
the ceiling of foreign exchange volume for the importers so that
the ministry can decide whether to grant the license or not.
</P>
<P>
With the new rule in effect, the liquidation in import, export
and transfer trade will be under the supervision of the state
loaning authorities to ensure that the trade involving foreign
exchange be conducted within the territory of Angola. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
