<HEADLINE> Iran's MPs Support Khamenei's Remarks against </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, September 23 (Xinhua) -- A group of 180 deputies of the
270-seat Iranian Majlis on Wednesday issued an open letter
pledging their support for the recent remarks by supreme leader
Ayatollah Ali Khamenei against Western "cultural assaults."
</P>
<P>
The letter, read at the open session of the
conservative-dominated Majlis (Parliament), thanked the Islamic
revolutionary court, which closed down the popularly welcomed
moderate daily Tous and arrested its several staff members last
week, the official news agency IRNA reported.
</P>
<P>
Tous, named after an ancient Iranian city, was banned for
publishing articles against the national security and interests
on September 15, the same day when Khamenei called on the
country's officials to repel western cultural assaults in disguise
of press freedom to target people's faith.
</P>
<P>
"I keep waiting to see what the responsible bodies will do"
with the group of the press that started targeting the people's
faith, Khamenei told a group of commanders of the Islamic
Revolutionary Guards Corps.
</P>
<P>
Targeting people's faith is a flagrant attempt to damage
Islamic principles and those of the Islamic system, the letter of
the Majlis deputies said.
</P>
<P>
It noted that those who write against principles of Islam
should be confronted as those working against security of the
country.
</P>
<P>
The letter urged the Ministry of Culture and Islamic Guidance
with the cooperation of Information (Intelligence) Ministry to
identify all those in the press who have targeted faith of the
people to enable the judiciary to deal with them within the
Islamic penal code.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the Guidance and Arts Commission of the Majlis
issued a statement on Wednesday, calling on journalists and
writers to abide by law and preserve values of the Islamic
society.
</P>
<P>
The commission called on the relevant authorities to adopt
necessary measures to prevent "destructive acts of certain
publications trying to poison the atmosphere of the Islamic
society."
</P>
<P>
The statement also called on officials to give proper
explanation of the duties of the mass media and a real definition
of social freedom in order to lead the society toward calmness
and tranquillity. 
</P>
</TEXT>
