Northern Ireland Mo Mowlam said Wednesday the Irish Republican
Army's arsenal would be scrapped and progress was being made in
implementing the province's peace deal on disarmament.
</P>
<P>
"I consider that progress is being made because it's no longer
a question of if decommissioning is going to take place -- it's a
question of when," Mowlam told reporters in Dublin after meeting
Irish Prime Minister Bertie Ahern.
</P>
<P>
The secretary also made clear that she believed the issue would
be solved in the end, just as a peace deal was eventually signed
in April after nearly two years of stop-start talks.
</P>
<P>
