begin to look for momentum and make progress step by step. That is
what's happening," she said.
</P>
<P>
David Trimble, leader of the Ulster Unionist Party and first
minister in Northern Ireland's new assembly, met Ahern and Sinn
Fein president Gerry Adams Tuesday in Dublin to try to break a
deadlock over the right of the IRA's political wing to sit in a
new cabinet.
</P>
<P>
"There is a very obvious difficulty at the moment," Trimble
said.
</P>
<P>
The IRA has consistently stated in public that it does not plan
to hand in its weapons, but is expected to destroy at least some
of its arms in the end in return for the release of IRA prisoners
within two years. 
