<HEADLINE> Hun Sen Warns Against Establishment of Interim Government </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SIEM REAP, Cambodia, September 23 (Xinhua) -- Cambodian leader
Hun Sen warned the opposition Wednesday that any attempt to form a
provisional government could be met with force.
</P>
<P>
"I have warned in yesterday's all-party crisis talk that no one
has the right to dissolve the current government," he said,
"Otherwise, we will consider it as a military coup d'etat and use
military force to deal with the situation."
</P>
<P>
Hun Sen made the remarks to reporters at the hotel he was
staying after attending the all-party crisis talk Tuesday, which
was presided over by King Norodom Sihanouk. He was staying in
Siem Reap to attend the inauguration ceremony of the newly elected
parliament, which is scheduled for Thursday.
</P>
<P>
He said that the formation of a new government is just a matter
of time and that the allocation of power is negotiable with the
principle of the CPP taking 60 percent of the government posts and
FUNCINPEC 40 percent.
</P>
<P>
Hun Sen said that he also told the opposition in talks Tuesday
not to oppose his candidacy as prime minister and said the current
government could rule for five more years if necessary.
</P>
<P>
"I warned in the meeting, don't dream about changing the
candidate of prime minister," he said, "The CPP had designated me
as the only candidate for prime minister. Now that the CPP wins,
I have every reason to take up the job in the new government.
This cannot be changed."
</P>
<P>
He also ruled out any possibility of forming a coalition
government with the Sam Rainsy Party, saying that it has totally
different political position with the CPP. 
</P>
