<HEADLINE> 4,757 Kg Drugs Seized in Nepal This Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, September 23 (Xinhua) -- A total of 4,757 kilograms
of drugs has been seized in Nepal this year, the Home Ministry
said in a press release Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
This included 4289 kilograms of marijuana, 463 kilograms of
hashish and five kilograms of heroin, said the press release
issued here at a press conference.
</P>
<P>
Home Minister Govind Raj Joshi told the press conference that
the government is fully committed to maintain law and order and
control irregularities and provide service to the people.
</P>
<P>
"Special attention has been given to control smuggling and
irregular activities which are said to be connected with political
and economic instability (in the country)," he said.
</P>
<P>
He disclosed that the committee formed to investigate the
irregularities at the Tribhuvan International Airport, the only
one of its kind in Nepal, had presented its report and those
involved would be punished.
</P>
<P>
He said that a police team had been formed for 24 hour service
in the Kathmandu Valley to control increasing criminal activities
and provide service immediately in case of natural calamities.
</P>
