<HEADLINE> Li Peng Meets With Lithuanian Procurator-General </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 23 (Xinhua) -- Li Peng, China's leading
lawmaker, met today with Lithuanian Procurator-General
Kazys Pednycia.
</P>
<P>
Li, chairman of the National People's Congress Standing
Committee, told Pednycia that the education and rectification
campaigns China's Supreme People's Procuratorate (SPP) and Supreme
People's Court (SPC) have carried out over the past few months
have achieved what he termed "phased results".
</P>
<P>
He said the campaign should be continued to achieve even
greater results which will enable China's judicial departments to
fulfill their responsibilities according to law and guarantee
effective law enforcement.
</P>
<P>
Li said that the procurator-generals from the two nation's had
reached a consensus during "productive talks". He expressed hope
that procuratorates in the two countries will enhance exchanges
and cooperation in order to contribute to the growth of friendly
Sino-Lithuanian ties.
</P>
<P>
The Supreme People's Procuratorate shoulders important
responsibilities for promoting and guaranteeing strict law
enforcement, said Li. He added that the SPP and the SPC carry out
their law enforcement activities under the supervision of the NPC
and its Standing Committee.
</P>
<P>
The NPC Committee for Internal and Judicial Affairs recently
heard work reports submitted by the SPP and SPC, said
Li, adding that the positive effect of their recent education and
rectification campaign "should be acknowledged".
</P>
<P>
Pednycia said the Lithuanian delegation has gained a better
understanding of China's judiciary through its current China
visit. He noted that Lithuania is also carrying out reform and can
learn from China's judicial practices.
</P>
<P>
He also expressed hope for expanded exchanges and cooperation
between judicial departments in the two nations. 
</P>
