<HEADLINE> CAST Celebrates 40th Anniversary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 23 (Xinhua) -- The China Association for
Science and Technology (CAST), China's largest scientific
organization with a membership of 4.3 million, celebrated its 40th
anniversary today in the Chinese capital.
</P>
<P>
Zhou Guangzhao, vice chairman of the Standing Committee of the
Ninth National People's Congress and president of CAST, recounted
the association's history over the past four decades. He noted
that CAST has engaged in extensive efforts to integrate science
with the economy.
</P>
<P>
CAST has provided important scientific and technological
services to planning China's industrial development, restructuring
and numerous key projects, said Zhou.
</P>
<P>
Various academic societies and associations under CAST have
provided services to hundreds of enterprises and factories.
</P>
<P>
The association has send large delegations of scientists and
technicians to poverty-stricken areas to assist more than 18
million poor people in 28 provinces.
</P>
<P>
Zhou said that CAST has promoted academic exchanges with
numerous countries and regions, including, Taiwan and Hong
Kong. Over 2,000 national academic conferences and some 200
international congresses are held in China each year.
</P>
<P>
The association has encouraged and supported young scientists,
and has organized three academic conferences and 30-odd forums for
their benefit.
</P>
<P>
A group of 100 scientists in their thirties received the Sixth
Science Prize for Young Chinese Young Scientists during today's
ceremony. Some 600 outstanding young scientists have won the prize
over the past 10 years.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
