<HEADLINE> Li Peng Meets Romanian Senate Chairman </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 23 (Xinhua) -- Li Peng, chairman of the
National People's Congress (NPC) Standing Committee, said today
that China is fully prepared to promote Sino-Romanian friendship
and cooperation on the basis of equality, mutual benefit and
respect.
</P>
<P>
Li made the remarks during a meeting today with the Romanian
Senate Chairman Petre Roman.
</P>
<P>
He said Chinese and Romanian people cherish their traditional
friendship and noted that the two nations enjoy close ties and
extensive contacts between high-ranking leaders.
</P>
<P>
Li briefed Roman on China's political and economic situation,
as well as the basic political system and strategy for governing
the country by law.
</P>
<P>
He said China values relations with Romania, and fully respects
the political system and development mode the Romanian people have
adopted.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that parliamentary exchanges represent an
important and positive part of bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
Li expressed hope that the two parliaments will enhance
cooperation in order to promote the overall development of
bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
The two leaders exchanged views on global economic and
financial matters.
</P>
<P>
Roman expressed admiration for China's achievements in reform
and modernization.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the recent battle against flooding fully
displayed China's mobilization and organization ability and the
brave and indomitable spirit of the nation's soldiers and
people. He said Romanian people have been deeply impressed with
the heroic effort.
</P>
<P>
Roman also called for strengthening friendship and cooperation
between the Romanian parliament and China's NPC and Chinese
People's Political Consultative Conference. 
</P>
</TEXT>
