<HEADLINE> edSignal's Technology Seminar AlliedSignal Holds Technology Seminar In Xiamen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAMEN, September 23 (Xinhua) -- A three-day technology seminar
organized by the U.S. high-tech giant AlliedSignal opened this
morning in Xiamen, a coastal city in east China's Fujian Province.
</P>
<P>
AlliedSignal representatives will explain the development of
engines, landing systems, aero-electronics, and machinery and hold
discussions with Chinese aeronautical engineers and pilots.
</P>
<P>
AlliedSignal will also hold a ceremony to mark the
establishment of the AlliedSignal TAECO Aerospace (Xiamen)
Co. Ltd, a Sino-U.S. joint venture that will service planes.
</P>
<P>
The company says it hopes that regular seminars will build a
bridge with clients and accelerate the development of air
transport in China.
</P>
<P>
Ruan Jianping, chairman of AlliedSignal, said that they chose
Xiamen as the seminar site because it is an active port with great
air transport advantages.
</P>
<P>
AlliedSignal is one of the 500 largest corporations in the
world. It produces facilities for the aircraft industry, spare
parts for automobiles, and advanced aerospace materials.  
</P>
</TEXT>
