<HEADLINE> ARATS, SEF Reach Agreement On Taiwanese Visit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 23 (Xinhua) -- The Association for Relations
Across the Taiwan Straits (ARATS) today reached an agreement with
the Straits Exchange Foundation (SEF) of Taiwan on the specifics
of SEF Chairman Koo Chen-fu's mainland visit in October.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Jincheng, secretary general of the ARATS, and Shi Hwei-yow,
vice-chairman and secretary general of the SEF, met at the Diaoyutai
Hotel in Beijing this morning.
</P>
<P>
In a press release that followed, Li Yafei, deputy secretary
general of the ARATS, said that the ARATS has agreed to make
arrangements at SEF's request that Koo Chen-fu pay his respects at
Sun Yat-sen's tomb in Beijing and visit Beijing University and the
Shanghai Stock Exchange.
</P>
<P>
Li said the ARATS hopes that the SEF will fix Koo's tour
schedule as soon as possible so that it can fully prepare for a
successful visit.
</P>
<P>
According to Li, the ARATS suggested initially that Koo came to
Shanghai before arriving in Beijing, to meet with Wang Daohan,
president of the ARATS, because Wang works in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
However, the SEF proposed that Koo came to Beijing first, and
the ARATS agreed with it on September 15.
</P>
<P>
The two sides will continue to exchange views on the specifics
of the visit this afternoon, he said.
</P>
<P>
Li said this morning's meeting was to make arrangements for
Koo's mainland tour, and it did not involve the topics of the
discussions between Wang and Koo.
</P>
<P>
The ARATS believes that the talks should begin with
negotiations on procedural issues of political talks, and any
political dialogue that is helpful to the peaceful reunification
and the development of cross-straits relations can be carried on.
</P>
<P>
Shi Hwei-yow said that both sides aired their views this
morning and that he hopes detailed arrangements can be made
this afternoon. 
</P>
</TEXT>
