<HEADLINE> Real Sociedad's Kovacevic Banned for Four games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, September 23 (Xinhua) -- Real Sociedad's Yugoslav
international striker Darko Kovacevic has been suspended for four
games , the Spanish soccer federation's disciplinary committee
said on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Kovacevic was shown the red card for abusing and insulating a
linesman a minute before the end of Sunday's league match against
Mallorca, which the San Sebastian side lost 1-0.
</P>
<P>
"It's rather excessive because it's the first time I've been
sent off in Spain. I was carried away because we were losing and
lost my head. I offer my apologies to the linesman, and my
teammates for letting them down." said Kovacevic.
</P>
<P>
However the Spanish federation still took a dim view of
Kovacevic's strong language and he got little support from his
club president Luis Uranga.
</P>
<P>
"The ban is fair and within the established guidelines. I just
hope it does not happen again," Uranga said.
</P>
<P>
Kovacevic was the team's leading scocer last season with 17
goals and was a key player to lift Real Sociedad to third and
getting a place in this season's UEFA Cup. 
</P>
</TEXT>
