<HEADLINE> Chinese and German Medical Exchange </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, September 23 (Xinhua) -- The 13th annual academic
meeting of Sino-German and German-Chinese medical associations
opened today at Jinan University in Guangzhou, the capital of
south China's Guangdong Province.
</P>
<P>
More than 250 Chinese and German medical experts will discuss
medical research and ways to prevent and treat Aids, during the
four-day conference.
</P>
<P>
The two associations, whose goal is to promote exchanges
between medical personnel in China and Germany, has held an annual
meeting since 1986. It is the first meeting focused on Aids
prevention and treatment.
</P>
<P>
Professor Liu Renhuai, president of Jinan University, said his
university has maintained academic exchanges with a German
foundation for 17 years. The university has sent over 100 medical
specialists to study in Germany and has had a dozen German doctors
who wished to study traditional Chinese medicine in China.
</P>
