<HEADLINE> HK Inks MOUs with Sweden, S. Africa in Monitoring Securities </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 23 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong's securities
watchdog has forged ties of cooperation with its Swedish and South
African counterparts respectively, it was revealed Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The Securities and Futures Commission (SFC) of Hong Kong
announced Wednesday that it had signed the Memoranda of
Understanding with the Finansinspektionen of Sweden and Financial
Services Board of South Africa on September 12 and 15, 1998
respectively in Nairobi, Kenya.
</P>
<P>
The three organizations were in Nairobi to attend the annual
general meeting of the International Organization of Securities
Commissions.
</P>
<P>
These signed documents establish a framework for mutual
assistance and facilitate the exchange of information between the
SFC and two other securities supervisory bodies.
</P>
<P>
The Finansinspecktionen regulates insurance, credit and
securities markets in Sweden, while the Financial Services Board
of South Africa supervises activities of non-banking financial
institutions in the country.
</P>
<P>
So far, the SFC has entered 32 similar cooperative arrangements
with overseas regulators. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
