<HEADLINE> Iraq Signs Contracts for Importing Oil Facilities </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BAGHDAD, September 23 (Xinhua) -- The Iraq has concluded 270
contracts to import oil facilities spare parts, under
U.N. Security Council resolution 1157, an Iraqi petroleum official
has announced.
</P>
<P>
In a statement printed wednesday by Iraqi daily "Al Ielam", the
general manager of the Iraqi petroleum marketing authority Saddam
Zein Al Hassan said that the contracts has been signed between the
Iraqi Ministry of Petroleum and foreign companies before mid
September.
</P>
<P>
He added that the Ministry of Petroleum had so far submitted 80
contracts to the sanctions committee, which had approved 24 and
the rest were either suspended or under consideration.
</P>
<P>
The U.N. Security Council resolution 1157 on last June 19,
permits Iraq to import spare parts for its oil facilities to the
tune of 300 million dollars. Since then, Iraq has been complaining
about the delay in the arrival of these requirements, particularly
that its oil facilities are about to collapse. 
</P>
