<HEADLINE> Asia's Biggest-Ever Jewelry Fair Opens in HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 23 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong is hosting Asia's
biggest-ever jewelry show although local traders admitted a
decline in exports this year because of the regional economic
slowdown.
</P>
<P>
Owing to a decline in overseas visitors to Hong Kong, the local
jewelry industry suffered a drop of 20 to 30 percent in overall
sales in the first six months this year than the same period in
1997, Leung Sik Wah, chairman of the Hong Kong Jewelers' and
Goldsmiths' Association, said here on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
But Hong Kong's jewelry exports to some specific areas showed a
considerable increase, with a rise of 13 percent for the Untied
States, he said.
</P>
<P>
Leung was speaking at a press conference after the opening of
the Hong Kong Jewelry &AMP; Watch Fair at the Hong Kong Convention and
Exhibition Center here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
One out of every three jewelry shops opened here closed due to
poor business or lack of interest in the business among the shop
owners' younger generations, said Aaron Shum, chairman of the Hong
Kong Jewelry Manufacturers' Association. Some of the shops managed
to survive after the property owners agreed to reduce the rents,
he continued.
</P>
<P>
But in the first half of this year, the ratio was about one to
one, which meant no increase of jewelry shops in general, Leung
said.
</P>
<P>
Shum brought about good news for the local industry. There had
been a 13-percent increase in demand for titanium alloy and white
gold jewelry products in the U.S. market, which could offset Hong
Kong's loss caused by the regional financial crisis.
</P>
<P>
And the steady market demand in South America and the Middle
East and an improving economic situation in East European
countries represents a good market potential for Hong Kong's
jewelry industry, Shum said.
</P>
<P>
As the exhibition space had been expanded by 55 percent over
last year to 42,000 square meters, the five-day Hong Kong fair
this year attracted a record attendance of 1,643 exhibitors from
41 countries and regions. The United States is the most active
single country in attendance, with 135 exhibitors participating.
Local exhibitors capped the field with an overwhelming attendance
of 765 exhibitors, according to the organizers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
