<P>
About 40 mutinous Lesotho soldiers were killed in clashes with
South African and Botswana troops that entered the mountain
kingdom Tuesday, the SANDF said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
At the invitation of the Lesotho Government, Pretoria sent
600 troops and Gaborone 200 to Maseru to help restore peace in
the mountain kingdom Tuesday Morning. 
</P>
</TEXT>
