<HEADLINE> Rural Telephone Users On Increase In East China Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, September 23 (Xinhua) -- More than 420,000 telephones
were installed in the rural areas of east China's Zhejiang
Province in the January-August period this year, a 52-percent
increase from the same 1997 period.
</P>
<P>
The increase is much higher than that for the urban areas in the
province and has brought the number of telephone users in rural
areas to 2.05 million, or one telephone for every 5 families.
</P>
<P>
Since 1996, the number of telephone users in rural areas has
grown by 29 percent annually, thanks to the growth of local
economy.
</P>
<P>
There is still great potential for phones in Zhejiang's rural
areas, analysts say. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
