<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0830 GMT, September 23 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG -- There was gunfire in the Lesotho capital of
Maseru Wednesday morning, apparently showing intervention troops
from South Africa had not yet put situation in the city under full
control.
</P>
<P>
South African Broadcasting Corporation said gunfire was heard
in Maseru again and people were running on the streets. Meanwhile,
more soliders from the Southern African Development Community's
intervention force have crossed the border into Lesotho.
(SAfrica-Lesotho-Gunfire)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS -- United Nations Secretary-General Kofi Annan
met with the members of the Security Council Tuesday evening to
discuss the latest standoff between Iraq and the U.N. Special
Commission in charge of dismantling Iraq's weapons of mass
destruction.
</P>
<P>
U.N. spokesman Fred Eckhard said the meeting was aimed at
discussing the idea of a comprehensive review of Iraq's compliance
with its obligations under all relevant Security Council
resolutions. He also announced that the secretary-general was
expected to meet with Iraq's Deputy Prime Minister Tareq Aziz at
the headquarters of the United Nations on September 28.
(Annan-Security Council)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BELGRADE -- Two encampments occupied by armed ethnic Albanians
were captured by the Serbian police force on Tuesday, the Pristina
information center said.
</P>
<P>
The Serbian police attacked the two bases of the Kosovo
Liberation Army (KLA), located in the Glogovac district and in
Srbica district, and killed several KLA men during the clash. They
also seized weapons and other military equipment, the information
center reported. (Yugoslavia-Kosovo-Fightings)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- The United States will sell jet fighters worth
Five billion U.S. dollars to Israel, the Pentagon said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
In a statement, the Pentagon stressed that the "I" models of
the F-15 jets, manufactured by Boeing Co., and the F-16 C and D
models, made by Lockheed Martin, would help maintain Israel's
military edge over its neighbors. Both F-15 and F-16 would be
equipped with sophisticated electronic targeting pods and increase
the Israeli Air Force's ground-attack capabilities, the Pentagon
said. (U.S.-Israel-Jet Fighters) 
</P>
