<HEADLINE> Share Prices Extend Gains on Singapore Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, September 23 (Xinhua) -- Share prices extended their
gains in thin trading on Singapore Stock Market Wednesday as the
benchmark Straits Times Index (STI) edged up 4.67 points to end at
900.99 points.
</P>
<P>
Total turnover decreased to 87.76 million units valued at
121.02 million Singapore dollars (70.06 million U.S. dollars).
Losers outnumbered gainers by 144 to 68 with 208 counters
unchanged.
</P>
<P>
ST Engg was the most active stock of the day as it had a
turnover of 10.60 million stocks traded. It was followed by ERL
w01 that had 3.75 million units done. KepCorp was next with 3.43
million counters changing hands.
</P>
<P>
SPH was the top gainer of the day as it gained 40 cents to
close at 13.60 Singapore dollars. SemCorp went up 17 cents to
finish at 2.61 Singapore dollars. TIH edged up 15 cents to end at
1.20 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, Asean 100 led the market's descent of the day
as it plunged to 2.20 Singapore dollars at close. Creative 50 slid
by 50 cents to finish at 16.10 Singapore dollars. Venture w99 shed
off 34 cents to end at 3.76 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said share prices fluctuated marginally amid absence
of fresh leads.
</P>
<P>
They also noted that some hedge funds were short-covering in
the market and individual stocks drew some attention.
</P>
<P>
Traders said the political tension in Malaysia still remained
at the back of investors' minds. 
</P>
</TEXT>
