<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Vietnam to Send 4,000 Construction Workers Abroad </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, September 22 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam plans to send 4,000
construction workers abroad this year, Vietnam News Agency
reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The current Asian financial crisis has caused a drop in demand
for Vietnamese workers in some Asian countries which usually
receive most of Vietnam's exported labor, especially Japan and
South Korea.
</P>
<P>
So far, Vietnam has a total of 50,000 laborers working abroad,
among whom 24,000 construction workers were dispatched by the
country's Import-Export Construction Corporation under the
Construction Ministry in the past ten years, said the report.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam started to export construction workers in the early
1980s with the first group sent to the Turkmenistan Republic of
the former Soviet Union. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
