<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kuala Lumpur Stocks Close Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, September 23 (Xinhua) -- Share prices on the
Kuala Lumpur Stock Exchange (KLSE) closed lower Wednesday after
some bargain hunting activities on cheap stocks in late trading.
</P>
<P>
At the close, the 100-quality stocks Composite Index was 9.19
points lower at 376.26, the all-share Emas Index dipped 2.32
points to 99.71, the Industrial Index dropped 19.89 points to
740.57 and the Second Board Index lost 0.82 of a point to 93.71.
</P>
<P>
Losers overwhelmed gainers by 465 to 125 while 100 counters
were unchanged, 228 counters untraded and 38 counters suspended.
</P>
<P>
The day's turnover was higher at 198.689 million shares worth
296.105 million ringgit (77.922 million U.S. dollars) from 115.901
million shares valued at 159.562 million ringgit (41.99 million
U.S. dollars) Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The main board turnover increased to 192.476 million shares
valued at 286.484 million ringgit (75.39 million U.S. dollars)
from 111.416 million shares worth 152.720 million ringgit (40.189
million U.S. dollars) Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The second board traded firmer with 6.213 million shares worth
9.621 million ringgit (2.531 million U.S. dollars) from Tuesday's
4.485 million shares valued at 6.482 million ringgit (1.705
million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
However, off market turnover declined to 3.595 million shares
worth 9.486 million ringgit (2.496 million U.S. dollars) from
5.535 million shares valued at 7.870 million ringgit (2.071
million U.S. dollars) Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
On a sectoral basis, consumer products accounted for 11.919
million shares traded on the Main Board, industrial products
22.650 million shares, construction 19.042 million shares,
trading/services 60.574 million shares, infrastructure 231,000
shares, finance 26.454 million shares, hotels 686,000 shares,
properties 25.717 million shares, plantation 7.975 million shares,
mining 1.117 million shares, trusts 117,000 shares, closed/fund
156,000 shares and loans 15.838 million shares. 
</P>
</TEXT>
