<HEADLINE> China Adopts World Environmental-Management Standards </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANYA, September 23 (Xinhua) -- The Nanshan cultural tourist
zone in Hainan City, the island province in south China, has
adopted the ISO-14000 environmental management standard.
</P>
<P>
This is China's first tourism enterprise to adopt such
standards, which relates to environmental management systems,
environmental inspection, and landmarks.
</P>
<P>
A management group formed to initiate and test the
implementation of these standards is already active, and domestic
and international authentication inspections will be conducted by
the end of the year.
</P>
<P>
The ISO (International Organization for Standardization),
headquartered in Geneva, was set up in 1947 and is a
non-governmental organization whose purpose is to set world-wide
recognized standards for a broad range of international
activities.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
