<HEADLINE> NPC Vice-Chairwoman Meets Norwegian Guests </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 23 (Xinhua) -- Peng Peiyun, a senior Chinese
legislator, met with a delegation of the Standing Committee on
Health and Social Affairs of the Norwegian Parliament, led by its
chairman John I. Alvheim, here today.
</P>
<P>
Peng, vice-chairperson of the Chinese National People's
Congress (NPC) Standing Committee, said China and Norway have
witnessed growing cooperation in economic, cultural, scientific
and technological and environmental protection affairs since the
forging of their diplomatic ties more than 40 years ago.
</P>
<P>
The two countries have also conducted academic exchanges and
cooperation in medicine, she added.
</P>
<P>
In addition, Peng briefed the Norwegian visitors on the
development of traditional Chinese medicine and pharmacology, and
epidemic control in the flood-stricken regions.
</P>
<P>
Alvheim said that traditional Chinese medicine and pharmacology
is being accepted by growing numbers of Norwegians.
</P>
<P>
Earlier today, Zhu Kaixuan, chairman of the NPC Education,
Science, Culture and Public Health Committee, met with the
delegation, and Zhang Huaixi, vice-chairman of the committee, also
held talks with the visitors.  
</P>
</TEXT>
