<TEXT>
<P>
JARKARTA, September 23 (Xinhua) -- Atlanta Olympic silver
medallist Mia Audina of Indonesia had her mind made up Monday to
carry on her country's flag in the badminton world by taking over
the role of pregnant Susi Susanti.
</P>
<P>
"I have determined to take badminton great Susi's place and to
concentrate on capturing the women's single title in the
up-coming Asian Games," said Mia after her training session
outside the country's training campus.
</P>
<P>
The teenager said: "I'll do my best to prove that I have the
ability to become Indonesia's top player and to score good
results in the Asian Games."
</P>
<P>
Mia made a sensational international debut by winning the
decisive match against Zhang Ning of China, bringing the 1994
Uber Cup to Indonesia at the age of 14.
</P>
<P>
The Indonesian teenager took the silver medal in the women's
singles at the Atlanta Olympics by losing to South Korean Bang
Soo-hyun.
</P>
<P>
Once ranked first in the world in 1997, Mia was plunged into
bad form this year as she lost her concentration in every match
against her chief rivals.
</P>
<P>
Mia took the Chinese Ye Zhaoyin, Gong Zhichao and Dai Yun as
her archrivals in the Asian Games as the Chinese overwhelmed her
several times. "The possibility of beating the Chinese still
exists if I can fully prepare for the Games," added Mia, who was
currently ranked 12th in the world.
</P>
<P>
Susi Susanti, 27, who has collected all kinds of titles with t
he exception at the Asian Games, vowed to take the last title she
eagerly wanted but had to step back from the Asian Games as she
found a fews days ago that she was on her way to motherhood.
