<HEADLINE> Kenya, Egypt Receive Byes in Africa's Soccer Qualifiers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, September 23 (Xinhua) -- Kenya and Egypt have been
given byes to the second round when the qualifiers for the
seventh All Africa Games starts in June next year.
</P>
<P>
According to the draw at the Confederation of African Football
secretariat in Cairo, the teams have been divided into seven
zones with every winner qualifying for South Africa' 99, local
press reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Zone one has two members of Algeria and Tunisia with Zone two
comprising Guinea, Mali and Senegal. The teams in Zone three are
Burkina Faso, Cote d'Ivoire, Ghana, Liberia and Nigeria while
Zone four has Cameroon, Central Africa Republic, Congo, Gabon,
Democratic Republic of Congo and Rwanda.
</P>
<P>
Kenya is in Zone five which also has continental champions
Egypt, Eritrea, Ethiopia, Sudan and Uganda. The teams in Zone six
are Angola, Botswana, Lesotho, Malawi, Namibia, Swaziland, Zambia
and Zimbabwe and Zone seven comprises only Madagascar and
Mauritius.
</P>
<P>
The winner between Uganda and Ethiopia will face Kenya in the
second round which will be played on a two-leg knock-out basis.
Uganda and Ethiopia face off in the first round between March 5
to 7, 1999 with the return match between March 19 to 21.
</P>
<P>
The second round matches in this zone kick off between April 2
to 4 with Kenya playing away. The second leg will be played
between April 16 to 18. Finals of this zone will be played
between July 9 to 11 with the second leg played between July 23
to 25.
</P>
<P>
The draw for the preliminary round of the Africa zone
qualifiers was also released by CAF. Kenya will play against
Tanzania in the first leg between November 27 to 29. The second
leg will be played between December 11 to 13.
</P>
<P>
Other fixtures for the preliminary round: Libya vs Mauritania,
Seychelles vs Mauritius, Kenya vs Tanzania, Uganda vs Sudan,
Botswana vs Swaziland, Namibia vs Mozambique, Mali vs Guinea
Bissau, Gabon vs Sierra Leone, Congo vs Equatorial Guinea.
</P>
</TEXT>
