<HEADLINE> American Mosley Retains IBF Lightweight Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September 22 (Xinhua) -- American Shane Mosley
retained his International Boxing Federation lightweight title by
stopping Argentine challenger Eduardo Morales in the fifth round
in New York on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
In the battle of unbeatens, Mosley kept his slate clean with
29 victories after his fifth successful title defense while
Morales fell to 26-1 after referee Arthur Mercante stopped the
fight two minutes and six seconds into the fifth round.
</P>
<P>
It was the 18th time in the past 19 fights Mosley stopped his
opponent early.
</P>
<P>
With both at the age of 27, Mosley stunned Morales with a
combination to the head, sending him to a sitting position
against the ropes 70 seconds into the round.
</P>
<P>
After Morales rose, Mosley continued the beating until
Mercente stepped in less than one minute later.
</P>
<P>
Mosley also sent Morales down in round three. Mosley caught
Morales with a left hook to the body and used another combination
to send him up against the ropes and down to the canvas. 
