<HEADLINE> Thai Tanasugarn Enters Quarters in Princess Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, September 23 (Xinhua) -- Tamarine Tanasugarn of
Thailand booked the first berth in the quarterfinals by beating
Henrieta Nagyova of Slovakia in the Princess Cup tennis
tournament here on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The 21-year-old Thai ace player rallied three times from a
service game down to eliminate Nagyova in straight sets,
including a tiebreaker in the second set 6-4, 7-6 (7-4).
</P>
<P>
"She is tough, she never gives up and she always runs for
every ball. I just tried to hang in there and play my game," said
Tanasugarn who ranked 47th against Nagyova's 23rd.
</P>
<P>
The Thai woman was down 1-2 in the first set, 0-2 and 2-4 in
the second set, but each time she broke back.
</P>
<P>
In the tie-breaker, she squandered three match points with
backhand errors, before hitting a backhand winner down the line
to finish off the match.
</P>
<P>
In the quarter-finals, Tanasugarn will take on American Amy
Frazier, who defeated Croatian star Mirjana Lucic Tuesday and
beat third seed Amanda Coetzer of South Africa 0-6, 6-3, 6-2 on
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Tanasugarn will play her fourth quarter-final match of the
year after losing all of the previous three. 
</P>
</TEXT>
