facilitate investigations into the same book under the Prevention
of Corruption Act.
</P>
<P>
Anwar was dismissed as deputy prime minister and finance
minister on September 2 and was expelled a day later from the
ruling United Malays National Organization (UMNO), of which he was
the deputy president, for "low morals." He was arrested by police
at his house here on Sunday night after leading an allegedly
illegal rally and procession which later erupted into rioting.
</P>
<P>
Anwar is currently being held under the Internal Security Act
(ISA).
</P>
<P>
Police said Tuesday that Anwar would be charged in court within
this week for sexual misconduct. 
</P>
