<BODY>
<HEADLINE> European Blood Alliance Established in Helsinki </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HELSINKI, September 22 (Xinhua) -- The European Blood Alliance
has been set up in Helsinki, capital of Finland, the Finnish Red
Cross said on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The organization aims to ensure blood security and blood supply
from volunteer blood donors and gradually achieve blood
self-sufficiency in the European Union (EU) members, the Red
Cross said in a communique.
</P>
<P>
The organization will also try to increase cooperation among
the blood services in EU member countries, it added.
</P>
<P>
The decision to establish the organization was made in Helsinki
on Monday by representatives from Finland, the Netherlands,
Belgium, Britain, Ireland, Luxembourg, Portugal, France and
Scotland.
</P>
<P>
The secretariat of the European Blood Alliance is based in
Helsinki. Professors Juhani Leikola from Finland and W.G.Van Aken
from the Netherlands were elected chairman and vice chairman
of the organization. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
