<HEADLINE> Ukraine, Georgia, Azerbaijan, Moldova Strengthen Frontier </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, September 22 (Xinhua) -- Frontier officials from Ukraine,
Georgia, Azerbaijan and Moldova have ended a quadrilateral meeting
in the Georgian capital of Tbilisi, with a pledge to strengthen
frontier cooperation.
</P>
<P>
According to information provided by Ukraine's frontier force,
the four countries agreed to coordinate their efforts to fight
international terrorism, trafficking in drugs and weapons, and the
illegal transportation of nuclear waste.
</P>
<P>
They also agreed to take part in the various activities and
international actions within the framework of NATO's "Partnership
of Peace" program.
</P>
<P>
They decided to set up a panel of experts to solve problems in
the four neighboring countries and that government leaders will
meet at least once a year to discuss their proposals.
</P>
<P>
Last year, the four countries agreed during an EU summit in
Strasburg to establish an informal alliance to strengthen
cooperation in geo-political and economic areas. 
</P>
