<HEADLINE> U.S. Plans to Sell $245 Million Arms Systems to Greece </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September 22 (Xinhua) -- The United States is to
sell Greece 245 million U.S. dollars of missile and rocket
launcher systems, the Pentagon announced Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The sale includes 18 Multiple Launch Rocket Systems (MLRS), 146
extended range rocket pods, 81 Army Tactical Missile System
(ATACMS) guided missiles and launching assemblies, 11 command post
carriers, 162 M26 rockets and other related equipment.
</P>
<P>
Prime contractor for the arms deal would be Lockheed Martin
Vought Systems, a unit of Lockheed Martin Corporation.
</P>
<P>
The Pentagon said it would provide the Greek army with an area
fire system for use against hostile artillery, air defense and
manoeuvre elements. 
</P>
