<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Half of Italian Women Harassed: Survey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, September 22 (Xinhua) -- Over 50 percent of Italian women
have been the victims of sexual harassment and four percent have
been raped, showed a survey released by the National Statistics
Bureau, Istat, on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Among the 20,000 women between the ages of 14 and 59 who had
been interviewed, 61.9 percent reported having been sexually
harassed, a term which also covered receiving obscene telephone
calls.
</P>
<P>
Based on the study's figures, Istat estimated that 714,000
Italian women had been the victims of rape or rape attempts, while
over 9,000,000 had been sexually harassed.
</P>
<P>
Almost 30 percent of rape victims were attacked in their homes,
10.5 percent in their cars and 8.1 percent at work.
</P>
<P>
And in most cases, the attacker was known to the victims: 23.5
percent of the victims said they had been raped by a friend, 17.7
percent by an acquaintance, and 14.5 percent by relatives,
partners or former partners.
</P>
<P>
The survey said 82.7 percent of the rape victims failed to
report the crime to the police and 93.2 percent of attempted rapes
were unreported.
</P>
<P>
Nearly 70 percent of rape victims said they had been unable to
get over their traumatic experiences.
</P>
<P>
Almost half of the women interviewed said they did not feel
safe in today's society.
</P>
<P>
The survey concluded that women between the ages of 14 and 24
living in northeastern Italy or southern urban areas were most at
risk from sexual violence. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980923.0239 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-23 </DATE_TIME>
