<HEADLINE> Sri Lankan Rebels Threaten Local Government Members </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, September 23 (Xinhua) -- The Movement for the
Liberation of Tamils which is affiliated to the Liberation Tigers
of Tamil Eelam (LTTE) in Sri Lanka has threatened all members of
local government bodies in the Jaffna peninsula, the Island
newspaper said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The movement in a letter has asked all Jaffna Municipal
Councilors to quit their offices forthwith.
</P>
<P>
Two mayors of Jaffna, Sarojini Yogeswaram and P. Sivapalan,
have been assassinated in recent months. On the more recent
occasion when a bomb was exploded in the Jaffna Municipal Council
premises on September 11, Sivapalan and 11 others top army and
police officers were killed.
</P>
<P>
About four months ago judicial courts in Jaffna, Mankulam,
Kayts, Point Pedro, and Chavakachcheri ceased functioning after
threats from the LTTE, the paper said.
</P>
<P>
The LTTE, which was routed in the Jaffna peninsula in May 1995
by government troops who now control of the peninsula, is making
every effort to destabilize the civil administration in Jaffna
city, according to the paper.
</P>
<P>
The death threats they issue have become more meaningful in the
light of the assassinations they have followed up with, the paper
added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
