<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Minister Says RMB Yuan Will Not Devalue </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 23 (Xinhua) -- A senior Chinese government
official reiterated today that the country's currency, the
Renminbi yuan, will not devalue.
</P>
<P>
Answering questions at a press conference today, Minister of
the State Development Planning Commission Zeng Peiyan said that
there is no reason for the yuan to devalue.
</P>
<P>
"A depreciation of the yuan can hardly help China's export," he
said, "on the contrary, it may have negative effect on the
country's economic development."
</P>
<P>
He said that a yuan devaluation might harm the confidence of
overseas investors' confidence in China and cause inflationary
concerns.
</P>
<P>
In addition, depreciation of the yuan may set off another round
of regional financial crisis and negatively affect the pegging
system of the Hong Kong dollar to the U.S. dollar, he said.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government has confidence in maintaining a stable
yuan, he added.  
</P>
</TEXT>
