<HEADLINE> Latin American Cities Favored by Conference Tourism </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA, September 22 (Xinhua) -- Buenos Aires, Rio de Janeiro,
Havana, and Santiago are the cities most favored by
conference tourism adherents in Latin America.
</P>
<P>
Conference tourism is currently considered to be the most
appealing form of tourism in the industry.
</P>
<P>
According to Chairman of the International Association of
Professional Congress Organizers (IAPCO) Vincent Van Wulfen,
conference tourism grew an average of 3.75 percent in the past two
years.
</P>
<P>
Van Wulfen is here to preside over an international conference
on organizing events, fairs and expositions, which opened Monday
and brought together some 220 delegates from 19 countries.
</P>
<P>
He said that conference tourism grew 9.96 percent in Buenos
Aires, 6.17 percent in Rio de Janeiro, 5.58 percent in Havana, and
4.58 percent in Santiago.
</P>
<P>
Other Latin American cities that have shown high interest are
Sao Paulo, with a 4.38 percent increase, San Jose, with a 3.59
percent, and Caracas with a 2.99 percent growth.
</P>
<P>
He concluded that the future of this industry lies in two key
words: competitiveness and flexibility. 
</P>
