<HEADLINE> China's Economic Target Attainable: Planning Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 23 (Xinhua) -- China will be able to realize
it annual target of eight percent in economic growth this year
given the government's stimulatory policies could continue to be
well implemented, planning minister Zeng Peiyan said today.
</P>
<P>
"Overall speaking, China's economic situation is good and the
measures the government has taken to expand domestic demand and
stimulate economy already started to take effect," said Zeng
Peiyan, State Development Planning Minister at an ongoing press
conference.
</P>
<P>
The minister added that August marks a turning point of the
economy, and all the economic indicators show that the economy was
already picking up in the month.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that the nation's fixed-asset investment growth
have picked up speed by the month, which rose to 26.9 percent in
August, four percentage points higher than that in July. Growth in
consumption also recovered to 13 percent in August, 1.2 percentage
points more than July. The growth of industrial added-value rose
by 7.9 percent, compared to a 7.6 percent growth in July.
</P>
<P>
"However, problems still exist in achieving the annual growth
goal, and we need to work even harder to solve them," the
minister noted.
</P>
<P>
To attain the economic growth goal, the government will need to
ensure more and efficient investment in key projects, achieve a
good autumn grain harvest, expand the domestic market and export,
adhere to a stable renminbi, and step up efforts in water control
and resettlement of residents affected by the summer floods, said
Zeng Peiyan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
