<HEADLINE> Mexico, U.S. Exchange Prisoners </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, September 22 (Xinhua) -- Mexico and the United
States are to have an exchange prisoners, relocating them to jails
closer to their place of origin, the Mexican Foreign Ministry said
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The exchange, from Tuesday to Friday, consists of 90 American
and 17 Mexican prisoners, said the ministry.
</P>
<P>
Under the 1977 Treaty on the Execution of Sentences, the two
countries can relocate prisoners that have been sentenced to long
prison terms.
</P>
<P>
Mexican prisoners sentenced to death in the U.S. are excluded
of the benefits of this treaty, and cannot be relocated. 
</P>
