<HEADLINE> 9 Brazilians Detained in Ecuador </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QUITO, September 22 (Xinhua) -- Ecuador's Immigration Police
confirmed Tuesday that nine Brazilians were detained at Quito
airport when they tried to enter the United States illegally.
</P>
<P>
Preliminary investigations said that the Brazilians had paid
about 800 U.S. dollars to "coyoteros", or illegal immigrant
traffickers.
</P>
<P>
The group was posing as tourists when they were stopped, but
later admitted attempting to enter the United States.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, Ecuador has become an illegal immigration
stopover. Illegal immigrants from South American countries first
travel to Ecuador before trying to enter the United States via
Panama or Mexico.
</P>
<P>
Ecuador has been consumed with illegal emigration fever.
About 25,000 Ecuadorans attempt to enter the United States
illegally every year. More than 200,000 Ecuadorans now live and
work abroad illegally. 
</P>
