years, according to an official release from the State Statistics
Bureau yesterday.
</P>
<P>
China is now listed No. 7 in terms of economic strength in the
world, said the release, adding that the gross domestic product
reached 7,477.2 billion yuan, registering an annual growth rate of
9.8 percent for the past 20 years.
</P>
<P>
-- The Standing Committee of the National People's Congress,
China's highest legislative body, held its third law lecture
yesterday.
</P>
<P>
Chairman Li Peng presided over the session which focused on the
characteristics and history of the nation's system of people's
congresses.
</P>
<P>
Li urged participants to enhance their understanding of the
importance of the legislative system in China, and stressed that
the people's congress system is the organizational form of the
people's dictatorship and the nation's principal political system.
