<HEADLINE> German Wust Wins Stage in Tour of Spain </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, September 22 (Xinhua) -- German Marcel Wust crossed
the finishing line first to win the 188.5-km 17th stage of the
Tour of Spain from Burgos to Leon on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Yet, Abraham Olano of Spain retained the yellow jersey as
overall leader with 22 seconds ahead of nearest rival Laurent
Jalabert of Spain.
</P>
<P>
Wust who won the 14th stage three days ago, packed in the
chasing group as local rider Matias Cagigas broke ahead after 89
kilometers and eventually surged ahead with a dozen kilometers
from the finish.
</P>
<P>
Wust paid tribute to the efforts of his team-mates Laurent
Brochard and Richard Virenque, saying: "During the stage they
told me to remain calm and they'd look after everything.
</P>
<P>
"They carried me like an armchair up to within 500 meters of
the line. I'm more sure of myself since my victory in Zaragoza.
I've proved that I can win, that I am the quickest."
</P>
<P>
Wednesday's 18th stage takes the riders on a 223-km run
between Leon and Salamanca. 
