<DOCNO> XIE19980923.0279 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-23 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Premier League Won't Block BskyB Deal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 22 (Xinhua) -- The English Premier League on
Tuesday dismissed suggestions it is trying to block BSkyB's
takeover of Manchester United.
</P>
<P>
Reports had indicated that the League was joining up with the
Professional Footballers' Association to oppose the bid in a
submission to the Office of Fair Trading.
</P>
<P>
League spokesman Mike Lee confirmed that a submission would be
made - as requested - to the OFT, who are investigating the
proposed takeover. But he added they would be doing so on their
own and would only be "seeking clarification on competition
issues".
</P>
<P>
Some Premier League chairmen have expressed possible
reservations about the takeover, suggesting it could lead to a
conflict of interests in future television deal negotiations.
</P>
<P>
Yet, for the time being at least, the League seems determined
to maintain the neutral position already publicly outlined by
chief executive Peter Leaver.
</P>
<P>
Lee said: "This is a matter, at this point, for the
competition authorities. We are happy to co-operate with their
enquiries." 
</P>
