<HEADLINE> World Bank Assists Lao's Infrastructure Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September 22 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank Tuesday
approved an interest-free credit of 27.8 million U.S. dollars
equivalent to Laos for a Provincial Infrastructure Project in
remote northern provinces of Oudomaxy and Phongsaly.
</P>
<P>
This project will help to improve the standard of living and
socio-economic potential of the provinces' poor inhabitants and to
gradually integrate them in the national economy. The project will
benefit an estimated 52,000 people in its 125 villages and
district communities in the two provinces.
</P>
<P>
The estimated project cost of 31.1 million dollars will be
financed by the World Bank credit channeled by the International
Development Association (IDA), the World Bank's concessionary
lending arm for developing countries. 
</P>
