<HEADLINE> Tanzanian FM to Attend Japanese Woman's Funeral </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, September 22 (Xinhua) -- Tanzanian Foreign
Minister Jakaya Kikwete will attend the Wednesday funeral
ceremony for a Japanese woman who was shot dead by car robbers in
Dar es Salaam last Thursday.
</P>
<P>
A government statement issued here Tuesday said that Kikwete
will deliver a condolence message on behalf of the government
during a two-hour ceremony to be held at the Japanese
International Cooperation Agency (JICA) premises in Dar es
Salaam.
</P>
<P>
Rieko Hanaoka's parents and family members jetted in Dar es
Salaam on Tuesday morning for the funeral ceremony.
</P>
<P>
They were met at the Dar es Salaam International Airport by
Japanese Ambassador to Tanzania, Keitato Sato and senior officials
with Tanzanian foreign ministry.
</P>
<P>
Hanaoka was killed by armed bandits attempting to rob her car
outside the gate of her residence in the Mikocheni area in the
northeastern outskirts of the city last Thursday night. Several
suspects have been arrested in connection with the incident.
</P>
<P>
The late Hanaoka, 30, was a medical technician with the
Maternal and Child Health Service Project financed by JICA at the
Dar es Salaam-based Muhimbili Medical Center, the largest
hospital in the east African country.
</P>
<P>
The statement said that Deputy Minister of Health Tatu Ntimizi
will also give a statement on behalf of the staff of her
ministry.  
</P>
