<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, September 22 (Xinhua) -- Visiting World Food
Program (WFP) Director for Africa, Mohammed Zajjari, Tuesday
praised Ethiopia for its proper use of the aid granted to it by
the WFP.
</P>
<P>
According to the Ethiopian News Agency, Zajjari made the
remarks during his talks with Ethiopian Prime Minister Meles
Zenawi.
</P>
<P>
A nine-member delegation of WFP's executive board led by
Zajjari arrived here Sunday for a five-day official visit during
which it will inspect the emergency and development food aid
projects in the country.
</P>
<P>
The delegation said Monday that it plans to give 47,000 tons
of relief food in support of those Ethiopians whose crops were
damaged due to climate change.
</P>
<P>
During the talks, Meles commended the joint activities
undertaken by Ethiopia and the WFP.
</P>
<P>
WFP's aid is based upon the food security program of the
country, he said, adding that WFP's aid will contribute to
Ethiopia's efforts to achieve food self-sufficiency. 
